overview: The user wanted to elevate the visual appeal of their sleep
  questionnaire app, moving it from a generic look to a more professional and
  calming aesthetic. I began by analyzing the existing design, identifying areas
  like the color palette, typography, spacing, form elements, and overall visual
  interest that needed improvement. My approach involved implementing a new
  sleep-themed color palette with deep indigos, purples, and teal accents, and
  introducing custom utility classes for gradients and shadows. I then
  redesigned the main  layout, enhancing the progress bar and
  card styling with decorative elements. The  was transformed into
  a more engaging welcome experience with feature cards and refined alerts. Key
  UI components like checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders were polished for
  better visual feedback. Finally, I ensured consistent styling across all form
  sections, replacing old gray boxes with new card-style groupings, and updated
  the  for a cohesive final presentation. The iterative process
  included a browser review to catch and address inconsistencies, resulting in a
  significantly improved, trustworthy, and aesthetically pleasing application.
